#: ../../commander.rst:85
msgid "Play Rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:87
msgid "The start of game procedure for Commander is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:89
msgid ""
"Players announce their choice of Commander and move that card to the "
"command zone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:90
msgid ""
"Players may then sideboard if the optional rules for sideboards are being"
" used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:91
msgid "Each player draws a hand of seven cards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:92
msgid ""
"Players may mulligan, using the modified :ref:`Partial Paris<partial-"
"paris-mulligan>` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:94
msgid ""
"Being a Commander is not a characteristic [:ref:`MTG CR 109.3 "
"<mtgcr-109-3>`], it is a property of the card. As such, \"Commander-"
"ness\" cannot be copied or overwritten by continuous effects, and does "
"not change with control of the card."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:96
msgid ""
"Examples: A :mtgtip:`Body Double` copying a Commander in a graveyard is "
"not a Commander. A Commander which is affected by :mtgtip:`Cytoshape`, or"
" is face down, is still a Commander."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:98
msgid ""
"If a player has been dealt 21 points of combat damage by a particular "
"Commander during the game, that player loses a game."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:100
msgid "This is an additional state based effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:101
msgid ""
"Commander Damage is cumulative throughout the game; nothing can reduce "
"the amount of damage a Commander has previously done to a player."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:102
msgid ""
"Because it is a property of the card and not a characteristic of the game"
" object, a card is still the same Commander even if it leaves the field "
"and returns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:103
msgid ""
"While effects can raise a player's life total, it doesn't reduce the "
"amount of damage previously taken from a Commander. (eg: :mtgtip:`Beacon "
"of Immortality`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:104
msgid ""
"Conversely, combat damage can be reduced, prevented, or replaced as it is"
" taken, in which case it was never dealt and doesn't count towards the "
"total taken from that Commander. (eg: :mtgtip:`Fog` or :mtgtip:`Captain's"
" Maneuver`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:105
msgid ""
"Commander Damage is specific to each Commander/Player pairing, not "
"combined across all Commander."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:106
msgid ""
"A player can lose if he or she is dealt 21 points of combat damage by his"
" or her own Commander (ie: under someone else's control)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:108
msgid ""
"While a Commander is in the command zone, it may be cast. As an "
"additional cost to cast a Commander from the command zone, its owner must"
" pay |mana_2| for each time it was previously cast from the command zone."
" (ie: Olivia Voldaren costs |mana_6| |mana_b| |mana_r| to cast for the "
"third time.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:110
msgid ""
"A Commander is still subject to the normal timing restrictions for "
"casting creatures (unless it has Flash or some other affect allows it to "
"be played at another time, such as Vedalken Orrery)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:112
msgid ""
"If a Commander would be put into a graveyard or exile from anywhere, its "
"owner may choose to move it to the command zone instead. Details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:114
msgid ""
"This is a replacement effect; the creature never goes to the graveyard "
"and will not trigger such abilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:115
msgid ""
"Commanders will move to the library or hand as normal; only transitions "
"to Exile or the Graveyard may be replaced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:117
msgid ""
"If a card is put into the exile zone face down from anywhere, and a "
"player is allowed to look at that card in exile, the player must "
"immediately do so. If it's a commander owned by another player, the "
"player that looked at it turns it face up and puts it into the command "
"zone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:119
msgid "Players begin the game with 40 life."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:120
msgid ""
"Commanders are subject to the Legend rule; a player cannot control more "
"than one legend with the same name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../commander.rst:121
msgid ""
